"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596081","Wales Office","false","2016-10-14","<p>The door is open to a growth deal for North Wales. The Government is looking carefully at proposals which have been developed by local partners in North Wales which could help to strengthen the region’s economy and make the most of its connections to the Northern Powerhouse.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2016-10-14T11:17:40.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596081/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596081/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/596081/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-10-07","Local Growth Deals: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what recent discussions he has had with ministerial colleagues about proposals for a North Wales Growth Deal.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","47038"
